# GVS — Supabase Migration Specification

**Architect OS | Growth Velocity Simulator**
**Version:** 1.0
**Status:** Ready for Implementation
**Audience:** Antigravity — Database Migration + Wiring Reference

---

## How to Use This Document

This spec covers three things in order:

1. **Schema migration** — rename existing tables, add new fields, update triggers
2. **JSONB payload definitions** — exact structure of every JSONB column
3. **Calculation architecture** — what runs client-side, what goes to Supabase, what Supabase handles natively

Execute the migration first. Do not begin frontend wiring until the migration is confirmed. The JSONB payload definitions in Section 2 are the contract between the frontend and the database — both must match exactly.

---

## Section 1 — Schema Migration

### 1.1 Rename Tables

```sql
ALTER TABLE public.growth_scenarios
  RENAME TO gvs_growth_scenarios;

ALTER TABLE public.saved_growth_scenarios
  RENAME TO gvs_saved_growth_scenarios;
```

Update all existing indexes and constraints to reflect new names after rename.

---

### 1.2 Update `gvs_growth_scenarios` (Runtime Table)

This table records every scenario execution. One row per run.

#### Add New Columns

```sql
-- Lifecycle status for GPT synthesis flow
ALTER TABLE public.gvs_growth_scenarios
  ADD COLUMN status text NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending'
    CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'complete', 'error'));

-- GPT-generated synthesis content (separate from deterministic implications)
ALTER TABLE public.gvs_growth_scenarios
  ADD COLUMN synthesis_content jsonb NULL;

-- Top-level score pulled out of results JSONB for indexing and analytics
ALTER TABLE public.gvs_growth_scenarios
  ADD COLUMN gvi_score integer NULL;

-- Whether this runtime record has been promoted to saved scenarios
ALTER TABLE public.gvs_growth_scenarios
  ADD COLUMN is_saved boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT false;

-- Timestamp of when is_saved flipped to true
ALTER TABLE public.gvs_growth_scenarios
  ADD COLUMN saved_at timestamp with time zone NULL;
```

#### Add New Index

```sql
-- Supports run-count queries for permissioning (count by user within time window)
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_gvs_scenarios_user_created
  ON public.gvs_growth_scenarios USING btree (user_id, created_at DESC);

-- Supports analytics queries on score distribution
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_gvs_scenarios_score
  ON public.gvs_growth_scenarios USING btree (gvi_score);

-- Supports filtering unsaved vs saved runs
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_gvs_scenarios_is_saved
  ON public.gvs_growth_scenarios USING btree (is_saved);
```

#### Full Table Definition (Post-Migration)

```sql
create table public.gvs_growth_scenarios (
  id                uuid not null default gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id           uuid not null,
  agency_id         uuid not null,
  name              text null,
  status            text not null default 'pending'
                      check (status in ('pending', 'processing', 'complete', 'error')),
  inputs            jsonb not null,
  results           jsonb not null,
  implications      jsonb null,
  synthesis_content jsonb null,
  gvi_score         integer null,
  is_saved          boolean not null default false,
  saved_at          timestamp with time zone null,
  created_at        timestamp with time zone null default now(),
  constraint gvs_growth_scenarios_pkey primary key (id),
  constraint gvs_growth_scenarios_agency_id_fkey
    foreign key (agency_id) references agencies (agency_id),
  constraint gvs_growth_scenarios_user_id_fkey
    foreign key (user_id) references auth.users (id)
);
```

